cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

The paper deals with social media and polarization, which suggests that it could fall under the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD), or Social and Economic Networks (cs.SOC). The use of visualization and recommendation algorithms suggests that it could also fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Computational Linguistics (cs.CL).
